HEADWORD: Boyau
<hw>Boy"au</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Boyaux</plw> or <plw>Boyaus</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>boyau</ets> gut, a long and narrow place, and (of trenches) a
branch. See <er>Bowel</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A winding or
zigzag trench forming a path or communication from one siegework to
another, to a magazine, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

